name: jupyter-black
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jupyter-black" %}
{% set version = "0.3.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/jupyter-black-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f0b0a60a8ea8302a8d65947aab691238addb2806a1d658eb5a98078feb44811c

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - black <23,>=21.9b0
    - ipython <8,>=7.27.0
    - python >=3.6
    - tokenize-rt <5,>=4.1.0

test:
  imports:
    - jupyter_black
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/n8henrie/jupyter-black
  summary: A simple extension for Jupyter Notebook and Jupyter Lab to beautify Python code automatically using Black. Fork of dnanhkhoa/nb_black.
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bryanwweber
